# gen75: flexible arith parser -- bilingual ratchet. Italian "cos'è" maps to
# "what is" via canonicalization; the compact-form and symbol-operator paths
# are language-neutral, so the same arith code answers.
> cos'è 2 + 2
< 4.
> cos'è 10 - 3
< 7.
> cos'è 2+2
< 4.
> cos'è 3*7
< 21.
# Word numbers still fall through.
> cos'è due più due
< I don't understand that yet.
